metadata.name: Quadrangle of My Being #19
metadata.description:
This project began as an exploration of how human beings across all sorts of cultures respond in remarkably similar ways in terms of associating sounds with shapes.  That’s a project I will have to come back to. Along the way, the outputs started to remind me of landforms seen from high above and topographical maps of imaginary terrain - the terrain of my own being.

Though the work is algorithmic through and through, I have used elements of my analog photographic work as a bits and pieces of some layers.  These photographic works are chemigrams, and are generative in their own right, arising from semi-controlled chemical reactions on dark room paper in the presence of resists and light. These chemigrams are the first topos of my being, and bringing them into this work emphasizes something I have long wanted to pursue - the rich interplay of my analog and digital practices in search of unexplored territory.

Explore some territory - you just might find the quadrangle of your being.

Collection Mechanics:
In the initial week after launch, holders of any of my past fx(hash) projects may mint free editions to the extent of their reserves on a first come, first served basis.  Beginning in the 2nd week, any unclaimed editions will be offered for public sale. 

Minting Instructions: 
1) Use the Randomized Params button to explore outputs.  
2) When a design emerges that you want to mint, lock the Seed Input param.  
3) Mint & enjoy. 

Parameter Descriptions: 
Seed Input: Each output is a unique result based on your wallet address and the seed value. If you record the seed for a given output as you explore, you can simply type in the recorded seed to retrieve it.

Project Details:
Created by Wanda Oliver (wandaoliver.tez) in July, 2023, this work is licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

The minter shares secondary royalties with the creator and a beneficiary.

Interactions:
Press [D] in live mode to download.
Press [S] in live mode to download a high resolution output suitable for framing.
Press [F] in live mode to toggle the frame on and off.

metadata.name: Self, Ego #178
metadata.description:
The third and final installment of the Self trilogy.

Ego is defined as: the one of the three divisions of the psyche in psychoanalytic theory that serves as the organized conscious mediator between the person and reality especially by functioning both in the perception of and adaptation to reality.

Please see attached fx(text) article or go to https://ty-vek.art/self-trilogy for more on concept/mechanics/etc. It’s a bit of long read, but worth it.

This is an fx(params) project and you will be able to choose exactly what your iteration will look like. For more details on why this is a params project and how to approach that, check out the article.

—————————

All projects are written in vanilla Javascript, composed as SVG and then rendered to a 2d canvas.

There might be slight differences in rendering from browser to browser. This is expected as they might translate the SVG slightly differently. Let's call Chromium renderings canonical. They also render faster there and we love that.

Press "S" to save a PNG.
Press "V" to save a SVG. (Chromium browsers render these pretty well.)

By default, these will render at 2400 x 3200 pixels. This is at density 1.

To render at a larger resolution you can append “&d=2” to the end of the url. This will double the resolution. You can also use 3 or 4 or whatever your browser can handle. Safari tends to have problems with this, so stick with Chromium based browsers (Chrome, Edge, Brave, etc.)

If you want to render as a square image, so it is optimized for ummm.. your pfp or something, you can append “&sq=t” to the url.

If you want to get rid of grain, just append “&g=n”

—————————

https://ty-vek.art/self-trilogy
https://twitter.com/ty__vek
https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/Ty%20Vek/articles

metadata.name: Slumbers #240
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.

metadata.name: Ries #388
metadata.description:
Ries is 500 sheets of paper. 
Ries is an cut-up text-artwork.
Ries is artwork generated by an algorithm based on seeded random numbers.
Ries is a digital artwork installed in 5 forms in exhibitions setting.
Ries is an NFT artwork. 

Ries is an artwork where I try bring together my experience of doing gallery exhibitions, my love for generative and copy machine art, DIY-punk aesthetics, NFT’s and chaos. 

The edition of Ries will be installed in different forms and collages in a gallery exhibition in Walden Kunstaustellungen in Berlin in July of 2022. Opening is at 8.7. 19.00, welcome if you are in Berlin.
/www.galerie-walden.de/

The seed idea for the project was the method of cut-up where a text (or something else) is cut into pieces and then rearranged to form something new. A modified Markov’s Chain algorithm makes a small text or a group of words from a pool of texts that include Art texts about cut up technique and generative art talk from tweets. These words form a visual bottom layer and then another layer of words samples the first, cutting it up and thus following the theme of the artwork.

Since the single iterations of the project are designed to be used in a collage, they come in various tone, density, detail and scale. One can test from the variations button and get a sense of what the generator produces. 

Controls in live view:
-Pressing  j exports the current image as jpeg
-Pressing  p  exports the current image as png

To change the detail level one can access the pixel density of render by adding ?pixDens=4 to the end of the URL in live view. You can of course you any number other than 4 also. I it renders just a black image, you have to lower the number, since it is then too large for WEBGL to render.

Designed to be best rendered on desktop Chrome.

Pricing info
22 tez - Includes a gallery shown, signed print sent to minter by mail or by telefax(!)
11 tez - A fair price for an artwork, also the minter can personally pick up a signed gallery shown print from the gallery, after the exhibition.
5 tez - 1/2 fair price
2 tez - bottom dollar

If you minted on lower tiers and would want a print, please contact the artist per twitter dm to “upgrade”. If you bought secondary, and would want a print, please contact the artist per twitter dm.

Features exist mostly to help with artwork pairing for the collectors.


Markov’s chain code core is based on Markov Me! By https://codepen.io/alexkramerbanjo , MIT License

Displacement shader based on the wonderful shader examples by Adam Ferris


The artist holds the right to use the whole edition of Ries for display purposes for future exhibitions without asking permission or notifying the owners of the NFT’s.

1.7.2022 in Berlin
Antti Pussinen

www.anttipussinen.net
www.twitter.com/antti_pussinen
www.instagram.com/anttipussinen

metadata.name: The Tiny Seed #19
metadata.description:
Biological and inorganic matter often grow from a tiny seed. After leaving the seed, the trunk unfurls into an array of possibilities. After some time has passed, the seed is reborn.

Some seeds can take longer to grow than others. All seeds begin in the middle.

A couple resolutions: 256, 512, 1024, 2048 (larger is rarer)
All other parameters change the behavior, colorization, and animation of each piece.
This is a larger edition, since the parameter space is very wide.

Each piece is lightly interactive. During growth, more seeds can be added by clicking and drawing into untraversed territory.

When viewing the piece live, you can press the 's' key to take a capture. Captures may be scaled to any desired resolution using 'nearest-neighbor' scaling.

Made with p5.js, p5Fbo.js, and glsl

metadata.name: Collider series - Primitive Expansion #123
metadata.description:
f(hash) = singularity
A glimpse on the primitive expansion of time and space.

500000 particles, pure JS/WebGL/ThreeJS code

Press 'B' to see the primitive expansion animation
Press 'S' to save a 4K PNG of current view (4096x2304)

metadata.name: Trouble with Bubbles #30
metadata.description:
Particles sticking and pushing, discolouring and interfering, wishing they were real bubbles and not just points on a plane.

Made with p5js and a modicum of love.

metadata.name: Circumscript #81
metadata.description:
It has always been a goal of mine to incorporate the worlds of physical and digital art together in a piece. And with circumscript I am the closest I've ever been. Circumscript uses a custom shader written to mix and "dilute" the colors on the canvas, thus creating a very physical feeling piece.

This dilution can be more or less depending on the edition, but always plays a huge role in the feel of the piece.


Happy new year.


----


[m] or [double tap] : opens the export/settings menu, use this menu to change the resolution, and make sure to press the reload button if you do.
[holding down] : zooms in on a certain area of the piece, depending on where your mouse/finger is. Use this feature to expore the complex textures of the piece in more detail, it's highly recommended to do this on a higher resolution setting.

The outputs can vary slighty per device, as there's a slight difference in how certain math gets interpreted on different devices with shaders.


----


Made with p5.js and webgl by Wouter Missler in 2022/3.

metadata.name: Oyoyiz #187
metadata.description:
Oyoyiz is an abstract composition generator. Available in 8 different color palettes and 2 styles (Organic and Brutalist), shapes made of a random number of segments are displayed on a grid. The name Oyoyiz was randomly generated.

Coded with Processing and P5js in October 2022 by @eltono and Michel - www.eltono.com

metadata.name: Univercell #27
metadata.description:
⚗🦠🌌✨

The center of a digital, quantified space emits 2 560 000 particles through a sequence of expansions, contractions and perturbations. 🌌

Once formed, the evolution of the Univercell can be observed through a series of animations in the manner of a documentary. 🎥

Each Univercell is a unique random and deterministic composition. 🔮

(Click ‘open’ and go fullscreen for best experience !)

🎄🌟🪐🌈☀




-----
* Mint preview *

Minter will get a 1920x1920 PNG bitmap and an infinite animation.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

The physics algorithms take around 20 seconds to generate one Univercell. During generation, a progress indication in percentage is displayed.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Unique generative and determinist animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Unlimited duration (no loop) / 6 documentary animations
- 20 seconds internal algorithm variations

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view frame (same ratio as window, max 1920x1080)

⚗ Empiric mode (empiric=on / see URL modifiers below)
Wheel/pinch : zoom in/out to observe the Univercell on different scales
Right click + drag : move the observation area
Keyboard "R" : enable automatic rotation of view

-----
* URL modifiers *

"&empiric=on"
Turn off animations and display a Univercell that can be manually explored.

"&demo=on"
Reduce the cinematics duration to 5 seconds. Allows faster cycling through documentary phases.

"&random=on"
Randomize documentary sequences order.


-----
@HAL09999 – December 21st, 2022

metadata.name: A long starry night #7
metadata.description:
This generative landscape is animated, some animations are very slow and take around 2 hours to loop.
This experience is best viewed fullscreen (click 'open' and go fullscreen) between FHD and QHD resolutions.

Press 'K' on the keyboard to go in the exploration mode. There you can drag the view with touch or mouse and orbit around stellar cluster.
Press 'K' again to embark on a travel following a celestial object.
Press 'SPACE' keyboard to take a screenshot (PNG) at current resolution.

attributes.name: In tribute to the science star

metadata.name: (recombination/perspectives)-I: Horizons #41
metadata.description:
🌊 🌞 🌈 🌅


    ( r e c o m b i n a t i o n  /  p e r s p e c t i v e s ) 


                     I :   H o r i z o n s


                            ✨ 🧬 🧡 ⏲







-----
* What/How *

2 560 000 particles are subjected to a succession of 64 energy bursts which scatters the points through space. 
The algorithm then stores 3 configurations of points, forming an entangled coherent system.
After few seconds multiple observation modalities are then selected sequentially to allow for dynamic and contemplative visualization.

-----
* Mint preview *

Minter will get a 2160x2160 PNG bitmap and an infinite randomly deterministic animation.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL / GLSL
- Unique generative, random and determinist animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Infinite animation
- Animation sequences duration between 6 and 60 seconds.

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view frame (same ratio as window, max 1920x1080)

Keyboard "X" : skip current animation sequence / next sequence

-----
* URL modifiers *

"&fastdemo=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 10 seconds instead of random durations.

"&slow=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 1 minute instead of random durations.

"&static=on"
Disables animation automatic start. Press "X" to start animations.


-----
@HAL09999 – January 25th, 2023

metadata.name: TRACE #30
metadata.description:
Introducing TRACE, an ingenious generative art project that weaves magic from the mesmerizing movement trajectories of the most fundamental geometric shapes, such as lines and arcs. Prepare to be captivated as we delve into the intricate interplay of geometry, motion, and filters, culminating in stunning and unpredictable still images. Much like life's unexpected encounters, stories, and moments, the final results remain veiled until the very last second, keeping us enthralled in a realm of perpetual wonder.

The name TRACE holds a twofold significance, each contributing to the essence of this remarkable creation. 

Firstly, at its core, TRACE is an amalgamation of diverse geometric trajectories, intricately intertwined to form an artistic masterpiece. The fusion of shapes and movements sets the stage for an awe-inspiring visual journey that unfolds with every stroke.

Secondly, and more profoundly, TRACE embodies the very essence of life's rich tapestry. Every individual, event, object, or fleeting moment that graces our existence leaves an indelible mark, a trace of its presence. These traces become the threads that weave our personal histories, forming the tapestry of our lives. Just like cherished treasures, the images composed of these past experiences are unique and invaluable, revealing the essence of who we are.

----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----

Save as a Picture:

Press “s”or “S” to download a PNG copy of the artwork.
